The paper deals with visual dialogue and proposes a new model for guessing the target object in an image based on a question-answer dialogue. This involves techniques from computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP), which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CV and cs.CL respectively. The proposed model also involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as state tracking and loss functions, which fall under the sub-categories cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
